Awesome

     A curated list of awesome READMEs

   Elements in beautiful READMEs include, but are not limited to: images,
   screenshots, GIFs, text formatting, etc.

Examples

     * [https://github.com/ai/size-limit]ai/size-limit - Project logo,
       clear description, screenshot, step-by-step installing
       instructions.
     * [https://github.com/aimeos/aimeos-typo3]aimeos/aimeos-typo3 -
       Project logo. Clear description of what the project does. Demo
       screenshot. TOC for easy navigation. Easy installation and setup
       sections with screenshots. Links for further reading.
     * [https://github.com/amitmerchant1990/electron-markdownify]amitmerch
       ant1990/electron-markdownify - Project logo. Minimalist description
       of what it is. GIF demo of the project. Key features. How to
       install guide. Credits.
     * [https://github.com/anfederico/Clairvoyant]anfederico/Clairvoyant -
       Multiple badges. Clean logo. Simple install instructions. Clear
       overview of the project accompanied by a schematic. GIF demo.
       Extensive code examples.
     * [https://github.com/angular-medellin/meetup]angular-medellin/meetup
       - Project banner. Badges for stats. Well placed emoticons.
       Contributor's photos.
     * [https://github.com/athityakumar/colorls]athityakumar/colorls -
       Multiple badges. Clean screenshots. Simple install instructions.
       TOC for easy navigation. Good contributor guidelines.
     * [https://github.com/choojs/choo]choojs/choo - Badges, clean, clear.
       Beautiful little menu above the fold with useful links. An FAQ
       inside of it for the main questions. Backers. Good language.
     * [https://github.com/Day8/re-frame]Day8/re-frame - Badges, logo,
       TOC, etc. Stands out by being a giant, well-written essay about the
       tech, how to use it, the philosophy behind it, and how it fits into
       the greater ecosystem.
     * [https://github.com/gitpoint/git-point]gitpoint/git-point - Clear
       description. Project Logo. App Store logos. TOC. Clean screenshots.
       List of features. Detailed installation process. Landing Page.
     * [https://github.com/Hexworks/zircon]Hexworks/Zircon - Dogfood in
       readme. Clear description of what the project does. Demo
       screenshot. TOC for easy navigation. Easy installation and setup
       sections with screenshots. Links for further reading.
     * [https://github.com/iharsh234/WebApp]iharsh234/WebApp - Project
       landing page. Clear description of what the project does. Demo
       screenshot. Simple install and usage sections. Includes an examples
       section with common uses and a mobile demo section.
     * [https://github.com/jakubroztocil/httpie]jakubroztocil/httpie -
       Description of what the project does. Demo screenshots. Project
       logo. TOC for easy navigation. Build badges. Quick and simple
       installation and usage sections. Includes an examples section.
     * [https://github.com/karan/joe]karan/joe - Project logo. Clear
       description of what the project does. GIF demo. Easy install and
       usage sections.
     * [https://github.com/Martinsos/edlib]Martinsos/edlib - Informative
       badges (build, version, publication). Concise description. Feature
       list. TOC. Screenshots. Concise instructions with examples for
       building and including in your project. Common code examples to get
       you started quickly.
     * [https://github.com/IgorAntun/node-chat]node-chat - Project
       screenshot. Informative badges. Clear description. Easy
       installation/use instructions. Live demo.
     * [https://github.com/NSRare/NSGIF]NSRare/NSGIF - Project logo. GIF
       Demo. Usage artwork. Usage code samples.
     * [https://github.com/php-censor/php-censor]php-censor/php-censor -
       Multiple badges, project logo, screenshots, step-by-step installing
       and upgrading instructions, TOC for easy navigation.
     * [https://github.com/rstacruz/hicat]rstacruz/hicat - GIF demo. Easy
       installation and setup sections with screenshots. Build badges.
       Great examples of use cases.
     * [https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts]ryanoasis/nerd-fonts -
       Clean project logo. Brief description at top. Sankey diagram, quick
       links, badges, OS specific icons, TOC, detailed release changelog.
     * [https://github.com/sebyddd/SDVersion]sebyddd/SDVersion - Project
       logo. Build badges. Documentation structuring for multiple
       programming languages. Usage examples.
     * [https://github.com/shama/gaze]shama/gaze - Project logo. Concise
       description. Feature list. Usage section. FAQ. Great API
       documentation. Release history.
     * [https://github.com/sindresorhus/pageres]sindresorhus/pageres -
       Project logo. Clear description of what the project does. Build
       badges. Demo screenshot. Simple install and usage sections.
       Includes an examples section with common uses.
     * [https://github.com/skywinder/github-changelog-generator]skywinder/
       github-changelog-generator - TOC for easy navigation. Concise
       project description. Installation and usage sections. Output
       example. Great feature overview. List of alternatives. FAQ.
     * [https://github.com/teles/array-mixer]teles/array-mixer - Clean
       project logo, badges. Table of contents. Contributing section. Many
       illustrated examples.
     * [https://github.com/nhnent/tui.editor]nhnent/tui.editor - Project
       logo. Clear overview of project features with a demo GIF. Badges.
       TOC for easy navigation. Colorful icons in front of titles.
     * [https://github.com/vhesener/Closures]vhesener/Closures - Project
       logo, cognitive funnel, animated examples. Color coordinated. Clean
       documentation.
     * [https://github.com/webpro/release-it]webpro/release-it - Clear
       overview of project features with a demo GIF. Badges. Expandable
       TOC. Usage description and examples. Contribution guidelines.
       Detailed releases.

Articles

     * [https://github.com/noffle/art-of-readme]"Art of Readme - Learn the
       art of writing quality READMEs." - Stephen Whitmore
     * [https://robots.thoughtbot.com/how-to-write-a-great-readme]"How To
       Write A Great README" - Caleb Thompson (thoughtbot)
     * [http://jfhbrook.github.io/2011/11/09/readmes.html]"How To Write A
       Readme" - Joshua Holbrook
     * [http://tom.preston-werner.com/2010/08/23/readme-driven-development
       .html]"Readme Driven Development" - Tom Preston-Werner
     * [https://changelog.com/posts/top-ten-reasons-why-i-wont-use-your-op
       en-source-project]"Top ten reasons why I won't use your open source
       project" - Adam Stacoviak
     * [https://medium.freecodecamp.org/what-i-learned-from-an-old-github-
       project-that-won-3-000-stars-in-a-week-628349a5ee14]"What I learned
       from an old GitHub project that won 3,000 Stars in a Week" - KyuWoo
       Choi

Tools

     * [https://github.com/noffle/common-readme]Common Readme - A common
       readme style for Node. Includes a guide and a readme generator.
     * [https://github.com/lappleapple/feedmereadmes]Feedmereadmes -
       README editing and project analysis/feedback.
     * [https://www.makeareadme.com/]Make a README - A guide to writing
       READMEs. Includes an editable template with live Markdown
       rendering.
     * [https://github.com/jehna/readme-best-practices]README best
       practices - A place to copy-paste your README.md from
     * [https://github.com/RichardLitt/standard-readme]Standard Readme - A
       standard README style specification. Has a generator to help create
       spec-compliant READMEs, too.
     * [https://github.com/zalando/zalando-howto-open-source/blob/master/R
       EADMEtemplate.md]Zalando's README Template - Simple template to
       help you cover all the basics.

Creating GIFs

   Embedding an animated gif in your README quickly demonstrates what your
   project does and catches the reader's eye. Here are a few programs that
   can help you quickly create gifs for your project:
     * [https://gifox.io/]Gifox - $4.99 - Cleanest UI, hotkeys, lots of
       advanced features
     * [https://giphy.com/apps/giphycapture]Giphy Capture - FREE - Easy to
       upload to giphy.com, slightly annoying UX.
     * [https://www.cockos.com/licecap/]LICEcap - FREE - Less intuitive,
       more features
     * [http://recordit.co/]Recordit - FREE - Simple, clean UI, but
       auto-uploads to [http://recordit.co/]recordit.co
     * [https://github.com/chjj/ttystudio]ttystudio - FREE - For
       commandline tools, a terminal-to-gif recorder minus the headaches.

